4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT CREATING THE MONTANA BLOCK MANAGEMENT
5 ENFORCEMENT NETWORK; ALLOWING LANDOWNERS TO OPT-IN OR OPT-OUT OF THE MONTANA
6 BLOCK MANAGEMENT ENFORCEMENT NETWORK; CREATING ADDITIONAL RESTRICTIONS
7 APPLICABLE TO LANDS ENROLLED IN THE MONTANA BLOCK MANAGEMENT ENFORCEMENT
8 NETWORK; REQUIRING THE DEPARTMENT TO PROVIDE ADDITIONAL EDUCATION OPPORTUNITIES
9 REGARDING THE MONTANA BLOCK MANAGEMENT ENFORCEMENT NETWORK; AND PROVIDING
10 RULEMAKING AUTHORITY.”
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
13
14 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Montana block management enforcement network. (1) The Montana
15 block management enforcement network is intended to establish a framework for assisting landowners enrolled
16 in the block management program established under 87-1-265 with enforcing compliance by hunters with the
17 landowner's rules and Montana law.
18 (2) Landowners enrolled in the block management program may opt-in to the Montana block
19 management enforcement network.
20 (3) By electing to opt-in to the Montana block management enforcement network, a landowner
21 does not waive any right to deny access to any property enrolled in the block management program for cause.
22 Additionally, a landowner may opt-out of the Montana block management enforcement network at any time and
23 may allow an individual who is subject to the restrictions of subsection (4) to access the landowner's property.
24 (4) Individuals accessing lands enrolled in the Montana block management enforcement network
25 shall adhere to all rules governing access to the block management property. Any conviction based on a
26 violation of those rules or any provision of Titles 45 or 87 by an individual while accessing lands enrolled in the
27 block management program must result in the following:
28 (a) for a first conviction, the individual must be prohibited from accessing all lands participating in
