1 the Montana block management enforcement network for the remainder of the current license year;
2 (b) for a second conviction, the individual must be prohibited from accessing all lands participating
3 in the Montana block management enforcement network for up to 3 consecutive license years; and
4 (c) for a third conviction, the individual must be prohibited from accessing all lands participating in
5 the Montana block management enforcement network for life.
6 (5) The department shall provide educational information to individuals accessing private property
7 under the block management program regarding the requirement to adhere to all rules governing access to
8 those private lands and the consequences for violating those rules on private property enrolled in the Montana
9 block management enforcement network.
10 (6) The commission may adopt rules to implement the provisions of this section.
11
12 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Codification instruction. [Section 1] is intended to be codified as an
13 integral part of Title 87, chapter 1, part 2, and the provisions of Title 87, chapter 1, part 2, apply to [section 1].
